S"With the Bank of Scotland Mobile Banking app, it\xe2\x80\x99s even easier to manage your Bank of Scotland UK personal accounts on the move. Following the release of version 2.0, some customers have reported problems with the app.\xe2\x80\xa2 Customers updating from a previous version may find the app icon displays incorrectly on the home screen, or disappears. If this happens, please look on your phone\xe2\x80\x99s full app menu to find it.\xe2\x80\xa2 Customers having trouble logging in should log in from their mobile browser by visiting www.bankofscotland.co.uk and selecting Log in.We apologise for any inconvenience we may have caused. We\xe2\x80\x99re working to release a further update to address these issues as soon as possible.Updates in Version 2.0\xe2\x80\xa2 We\xe2\x80\x99ve seen the feedback, and introduced a little fix to help repair the crashing and connectivity issues that some users have been experiencingUpdates in Version 1.3\xe2\x80\xa2 Removes minor installation bugBased on your feedback, we\xe2\x80\x99ve made additional improvements to Mobile Banking. Now you can:\xe2\x80\xa2 View your transaction history\xe2\x80\xa2 Register for Internet Banking\xe2\x80\xa2 Change some of your personal details\xe2\x80\xa2 Manage your existing overdrafts\xe2\x80\xa2 Switch to the desktop site and backEven if you\xe2\x80\x99re not a Bank of Scotland customer, you can still use the app to find any Bank of Scotland branch or ATM and LINK ATMs in the UK. With the latest updates you can now:\xe2\x80\xa2 Find a Bank of Scotland branch and ATMs or LINK ATMs in the UK \xe2\x80\xa2 Log in with your usual Internet Banking details\xe2\x80\xa2 View balances and transaction history\xe2\x80\xa2 Check your credit card limit\xe2\x80\xa2 Make transfers between your Bank of Scotland UK personal current and savings accounts\xe2\x80\xa2 Set up and make payments\xe2\x80\xa2 Manage your existing overdraft\xe2\x80\xa2 Find useful Bank of Scotland phone numbers- And enjoy a high level of security. You don\xe2\x80\x99t need to register to use the app Mobile Banking services if you\xe2\x80\x99re already a Bank of Scotland personal Internet Banking customer. Simply log in using your normal Internet Banking details wherever you have signal. If you haven\xe2\x80\x99t registered for Internet Banking, you can do so using the app. Keeping you safe onlineWe use the latest online security measures to protect your money, your personal information and your privacy. We also have a banking guarantee that ensures you won\xe2\x80\x99t be out-of-pocket if you're a victim of online fraud. Some things you can do to protect yourself online:\xe2\x80\xa2 Treat mobile security as seriously as you treat computer security.\xe2\x80\xa2 Take care when entering personal information in public places.\xe2\x80\xa2 Find out what software your phone provider offers to protect you online.\xe2\x80\xa2 Switch off Bluetooth when you\xe2\x80\x99re not using it\xe2\x80\xa2 Don\xe2\x80\x99t accept or open any applications or MMS messages from unknown senders \xe2\x80\xa2 Use your mobile phone\xe2\x80\x99s security lock or PINImportant informationThis app and Mobile Banking are designed for use in the UK. We don\xe2\x80\x99t charge you for using this app but your mobile operator may charge for some services. Services may be affected by phone signal and functionality.The Branch/ATM finder uses location based services.  We, LINK Scheme and/or Google may get data about your location (i.e. GPS signals from your mobile device) or data that can be used to approximate your location (such as your mobile ID).The Mobile Banking service in this app is available to our UK personal Internet Banking customers only. Use of it is subject to our Internet Banking terms and conditions www.bankofscotland.co.uk/aboutonline/online-conditions By using this app or providing information to us, you consent to the use and transfer of your information as set out above and in our privacy policy www.bankofscotland.co.uk/securityandprivacy/privacy This app and Mobile Banking are operated by Bank of Scotland plc (registered in Scotland (No. SC327000) rRegistered office: The Mound, Edinburgh, EH1 1YZ. Authorised and regulated by the Financial Services Authority.Recent changes:Following the release of version 2.0, some customers have reported problems with the app.\xe2\x80\xa2 Customers updating from a previous version may find the app icon displays incorrectly on the home screen, or disappears. If this happens, please look on your phone\xe2\x80\x99s full app menu to find it\xe2\x80\xa2 Customers having trouble logging in should log in from their mobile browser by visiting www.bankofscotland.co.ukWe apologise for any inconvenience we may have caused, and are working to release a fix asap."
